<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Auto heights with inline boxes</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#block-root-margin" />
        <meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Line height of block box is based on inline box top and bottom edges." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                font: 20px/1em ahem;
            }
            #div1
            {
                background-color: blue;
                color: blue;
            }
            .c1
            {
                display: inline;
            }
            #div1
            {
                float: left;
                height: auto;
                width: 4em;
            }
            #div2
            {
                background: green;
                height: 1em;
                width: 6em;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box has the same height as the green box.</p>
        <div id="div1">
            <span class="c1">X</span>
            <span class="c1">X</span>
        </div>
        <div id="div2"></div>
    </body>
</html>